<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - INSTALLATION - OIL PICKUP TUBE
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
        <title>OIL PICKUP TUBE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil pick-up tube as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Using a new gasket, place gasket onto oil pick-up tube (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050756">7.56</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Align holes of oil pick-up tube with two (2) holes in front cover. Secure oil pick-up
                    tube to front cover.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050755" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2393" filename="../figeg2/eg2393.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.55.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Dial Indicator</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Rear Thrust Bearing Cap</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Crankshaft</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Pry Bar</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050756" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2395" filename="../figeg2/eg2395.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.56.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Gasket</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Oil Pick-Up Tube</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Crankcase</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Align oil pick-up tube with support bracket and secure using one (1) bolt. Tighten to
                    special torque value.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten two (2) front bolts to special torque value. (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e105_167.xml" xrefid="ef1050757">7.57</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    )
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
